Next up is James Dobbyn, winner of the Polynesian Music Award of Excellence and IX Award Best Pop Artist. I have never forgotten his single from the mid '80s - Slice Of Heaven.

Here's James performing Often in Small Spaces: a song he wrote about life in Aotearoa

and Here's one of my favourite James Dobyn Songs - Slice of Heaven
Daley Thorne - soon to be a lasting legacy of New Zealand talent
Daley Thorne rightly earned the award as Miss NZ Earth because she is just so adorable. Seeing her here with her parents reminds me so much of my own teenage self. She's my eternal Dolly Parton look alike. Besides making my list of greatest Idol winners (both Idol and NZ Idol I am talking about here), Daley has been winning hearts ever since she took up her Miss NZ Earth trophy and title.

Her teenage diary has been immortalized so that we can now all share in her utter teen awkwardness. Daley emigrated to Japan in 2008 to pursue a singing career and is now based in Los Angeles.

I pick up the CD she sent us and read the lyrics inside. An interpretation of "dress up", Chamber of Secrets is Daley's play on the swing and love ball
